# .trivyignore — waivers for Trivy findings you have reviewed and accepted.
#
# Add one CVE ID per line. Comments above the ID are part of the file's git
# history and become your audit trail for why a finding is not being fixed.
#
# Example:
#
#   # CVE-2025-12345 — libcurl in upstream base. Not reachable from our
#   # deployment (container runs behind mTLS ingress, no outbound HTTP).
#   # Revisit 2026-08 when upstream bumps the base image.
#   CVE-2025-12345
#
# Leave this file empty (except for comments) until you actually need a waiver.
# A waiver without a reason is just a mute button, not evidence.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CVE-2026-4800 — lodash _.template code injection / prototype pollution.
#   lodash < 4.18.0, fixed in 4.18.0. GHSA-r5fr-rjxr-66jc. The CVE-2021-23337
#   fix validated the `variable` option of _.template but not the
#   `options.imports` key names; an attacker who controls those keys can
#   inject code.
#
# Where it surfaces: a transitive npm dependency of the hub frontend
#   (internal/site, bun.lock / package-lock.json). Flagged by the Trivy *fs*
#   scan of the cloned source, NOT the image scan — the runtime image is
#   scratch + Go binary with the frontend embedded as minified client-side
#   JS, so there is no lodash lockfile/package in the published image.
#
# Why waived, not fixed:
#   1. Mirror policy. We do not override upstream's lockfiles — bumping lodash
#      is henrygd's call. Pinning a different version here would diverge our
#      build from upstream behaviour, which is out of scope for a mirror.
#      (Same stance as the mirror-uptime-kuma npm-layer waivers.)
#   2. Sink not reached in a server-exploitable way. lodash here is bundled
#      client-side frontend code; the _.template imports-key sink requires the
#      application to call _.template with attacker-controlled `imports` keys,
#      which is not how the Beszel dashboard uses it. Not a server-side RCE in
#      the hub.
#
# Action: this waiver exists to unblock the initial mirror build. Revisit
# 2026-09-14, or sooner when upstream bumps lodash to >= 4.18.0 (at which
# point this line should be removed and the finding will clear on its own).
CVE-2026-4800
